Sleepwalkers are non-interactive Morytanians wandering towards the Sisterhood Sanctuary in their sleep. They were added as a teaser prior to the release of The Nightmare.

They spawn in one of 4 locations and walk to the entrance of the Sisterhood Sanctuary where they despawn:

  • In front of the Taxidermist's house in Canifis, walking towards Andras's boat north of Port Phasmatys and riding it to Slepe.
  • Outside the Crombwick Manor.
  • South-west of the entrance to Ver Sinhaza.
  • Outside the Canifis clothing shop walking to Andras's boat.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The sleepwalkers' examine text is a reference to Bring Me the Horizon's song Sleepwalking.[1]

References[edit | edit source]

  1. ↑ Jagex. Mod Tide's Twitter account. 7 May 2020. (Archived from the original on 7 May 2020.) Mod Tide: "[The examine text of the sleepwalkers that you can find walking to the Nightmares entrance is a reference to a song.] [BMTH - Sleepwalking?] You got it."

'''Sleepwalkers''' are non-interactive [[Morytania]]ns wandering towards the [[Sisterhood Sanctuary]] in their sleep. They were added as a teaser prior to the release of [[The Nightmare]].

They spawn in one of 4 locations and walk to the entrance of the [[Sisterhood Sanctuary]] where they despawn:
* In front of the [[Taxidermist]]'s house in [[Canifis]], walking towards [[Andras]]'s boat north of [[Port Phasmatys]] and riding it to Slepe.
* Outside the [[Crombwick Manor]].
* South-west of the entrance to [[Ver Sinhaza]].
* Outside the [[Canifis]] [[Barkers' Haberdashery|clothing shop]] walking to Andras's boat.

==Trivia==
* The sleepwalkers' examine text is a reference to {{WP|Bring Me the Horizon}}'s song ''Sleepwalking''.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Tide|url=https://twitter.com/JagexTide/status/1258364433212100608|date=7 May 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/zWxlj|archivedate=7 May 2020|quote=[The examine text of the sleepwalkers that you can find walking to the Nightmares entrance is a reference to a song.] [BMTH - Sleepwalking?] You got it.}}
